casebody.data:
Peter F. DIPAOLO, Plaintiff,
v.
NEW JERSEY PHYSICIANS UNITED RECIPROCAL EXCHANGE, Defendant-Respondent,
and
Crystal Evans, Intervenor-Movant. M-813/814 September Term 2017
080441 Supreme Court of New Jersey. March 12, 2018

ORDER

It is ORDERED that the motion for leave to appeal (M-813) is granted and the matter is summarily remanded to the Appellate Division to consider on the merits. Jurisdiction is not retained; and it is further

ORDERED that the motion for a stay (M-814) is granted pending appeal in the Appellate Division. A request for a further stay must be filed before that court.
